title Notes are fully versioned — invariant, not convention
edge explains commit:3628ee983ca6251238bf9b43b33e57fcda076089

Because notes are invisible (GitHub doesn't render them, most
tools ignore them), versioning is MORE important, not less. You can't
glance at a diff to notice something disappeared. The auto-supersede
in the tool and the invariants in the spec ensure that even sloppy
usage (git notes add -f) can't silently destroy data. The old blob
is always one git cat-file away via the supersedes chain.
